Jančura denies that the two seats were sold for the stewards.
"These places cannot be reserved for long distance connections, they are blocked."
Company wants to sue truck drivers.
With compensation for the young woman's family, the agency will not wait for the court ruling, but it also expects financial compensation from the guilty party.
A change in the law?
Not in sight
A more precise regulation of the movement of stewards on board a bus could bring about a legal regulation on which a thirty-member expert team of the Ministry of Transport has been working for over a year.
"However, this has not yet reached a concrete conclusion.
Buses are also not necessarily on the agenda, rather the point system, the top speed on the highway and the use of mobile phones while driving," said Hořín.
"The Ministry of Transport does not consider the work of the stewards as something that could significantly endanger the safety of passengers," says Hanzelka, with the control of the safety of buses being the competence of the police and the health and safety authorities.
