It looked like they wouldn't have to stop with the charge of more than two thousand kilos of hashish.
The police followed her and arrested one of the drivers, the man who is 28 years old, known as A. A. J., as reported by the Ministry of the Interior of the Basque State.
The person arrested was accused of drug trafficking and forgery of official documents.
The incident occurred when the traffic police of the Álava region had already completed the traffic control on the N-1 and passed through the city of Armiñon.
They decided to stop a car to carry out the route control. The driver did not follow the instructions, suddenly increased the speed and tried to escape control.
The police started the persecution until the car stopped at the edge strip after a few kilometers. At that moment, the drivers got out of the car to flee via a country road to a forest area.
The police of Ertzaintza finally caught up with one of the two. In the car, an Iveco Daily, the drug traffickers transported 2,178 kilos of hashish, which was confiscated by the police.
The front part of the car was loaded with hashish bundles, which were later directed to the exact laboratory analysis and weighing of the bundles to other police stations.
In addition, the officials found that the license plate was 'double', so that it did not correspond to the license plate indicated in the car papers, which is why an additional arrest was carried out for forgery of official documents.
The police in Ertzaintza City continue the investigation to investigate the arrest of the second suspect, who, as already mentioned, was able to escape, but also to determine the origin of the seized drugs.
The arrested 28-year-old A. A. J. was taken to a police station for interrogation. He will be brought before the prison judge in the next hours.
Actress Heather Locklear was arrested for driving under the effect of an unknown medication.
The actress Heather Locklear, known for the role of Amanda from the series "Melrose Place", was arrested this weekend in Santa Barbara (California) for driving under the effect of an unknown medication.
A witness observed how she tried to get out of her parking space in Montecito in a rather strange way, California traffic police spokesman reported to the magazine 'People'.
The witness told in detail that Locklear pushed 'after 4:30 p.m. throttle and made a lot of noise by trying to move her car backwards or forwards out of the parking space, and as she was driving backwards, she grabbed her sunglasses a few times.'
A little later, the witness, who had probably not recognized the actress at the beginning, saw Locklear stopping on a nearby road and exiting the car.
The witness was the person who notified the emergency service because she 'feared of Locklears'.
When the police patrol arrived, they found the actress sitting in her car, standing across the street blocking traffic.
'She seemed disoriented,' so they took the police to a special drug and alcohol center to take a test.
According to a police spokesman, the actress showed co-operative, excessive alcohol consumption was ruled out from the first moment. 'Following the first observations of the officials, we believe that Locklear was under the influence of an unknown drug,' said the spokesman.
Locklear was arrested on suspicion of driving under the influence of an indefinite substance that could not be determined and taken to a local detention centre around 7 p.m.
Two months ago, Locklaer was released from the Arizona hospital after treatment, where she was treated for anxiety and depression.
