The drivers, who can fall back because of the alcohol level, will have to install the 'Alcolock'.
The authorities order that the driver who had three official penalties for the alcohol level installs this system in his car, which forbids him to start the car in a drunken state. If he is alcoholized, the car does not start.
The initiative was announced last month in June and is already part of the report of the Attorney General. According to her, it is a pilot project, which will last for a year.
The purpose is to rehabilitate the driver, which is why he gets a course for the re-education of traffic behaviour.
In addition to the Attorney General's Office, experience has shown that the Ministry of Transport and the Foundation of the Technical Institute for the Safety of Automobiles will also participate.
According to statistics, between 30-75% of motorists, who were reported more than once because of driving under alcohol influence, returned to driving.
The `alcolock' would prevent this because it is a system connected to the car, it measures the alcohol content in the exhaled air and prevents autostart when the driver has taken alcohol test; or when an alcohol concentration is detected that is higher than allowed.
It costs more than EUR 1 000, the costs are borne by the person who imposes the penalty.
In this context, a study conducted in the USA in 2007 has shown that cars equipped with these devices prevent up to 65% of the rule violations already in the first year after its introduction.
In Spain, 115 lives are expected to be saved each year.
The measure is limited to administrative sanctions for two reasons: to tackle this behavior before it becomes a criminal offence.
And in order to facilitate their implementation, a legal reform can be implemented by ordinary means, and yet a reform of the Basic Law is called for, which is necessary for the prosecution process.
The device is still available in the Spanish markets, in no business, although it has already been installed in some commercial vehicles and public transport vehicles.
Tomorrow of all days, the House of Deputies will vote on the initiative of the Spanish Socialist Workers' Party, which proposes to install this system in school buses, which has already been done in France.
